					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For the record, here's the Japanese Maniac Mansion password entry screen:
<br /><img src="http://bisqwit.iki.fi/cv2fin/comparative_screenshots/maniacj.png" alt="Image" />
<br />66 symbols, filled into (6+8+7)*5-1 = 104 slots, as indicated by Lidnariq earlier. That's almost twice the amount of information carried in an SMS, considering that the Japanese symbols correspond to syllables.
<br />
<br />One may wonder, did they not even try optimizing the storage? For example eliminating irrelevant data or impossible combinations...</div>

